Package edu.harvard.hms.dbmi.bd2k.irct.model.query

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClauseAbstract
    An abstract class that represents any clause that can be part of a query.
    JoinClause
    The Join clause allows the user to combine 2 different subqueries on given set of fields, or relationship using a given type of join.
    JoinType
    The join type class provides a way for the IRCT application to keep track of which joins can be used.
    PredicateType
    The predicate type class provides a way for the IRCT application to keep track of which predicates can be used.
    PredicateTypeValue
    A predicate type value that is associated with a predicate
    Query
    The query class represents any query against any individual or group of resources.
    SelectClause
    The select clause provides a list of parameters that should be returned by the query.
    SubQuery
    A sub query may be part of a query or another sub query.
    WhereClause
    The where clause contains information used in a query to filter upon the data.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LogicalOperator
    Logical Operator enumerations provide a choice of three different operators that can be used to combine different where clauses or other parts of a query
    PredicateTypeValueDataType
    A list of possible predicate types available to the predicate
